reviews: Great light and rechargeable. Very bright, but not too bright. Battery or charging last long. Cones with 2 mini charging chords. No plug extensions though, but will work on any USB port, even a laptop if your commuting from work at nigh. Red and Green charge indicators. Cons. Boxxy Light.
Logo looked a little torn in the seems, thick ass Toque and fit was weird and bulky and over all masive Toque. Filed this under donations. "Yes I'm Canadian and said to Toque"
Good price for a 32g
DECENT Hoodie for the price. Only Isuse was the Pockets were so tiny. You could barely keep your keys in them without having them fall out.
No cons, no pros
Gifted these to my girlfriend after owning a set. She loves them just as much as I do. One of the best water bases paint markers to use.

review_title: Nice Stick by Questlove / Vic Firth
reviews: These are nice drumsticks model for Questlove, a little long for me in length for playing as I like to play a little lower to my kit. Good thickness to them, but they get chewed up easily on the hi-hats. I'll probably just go with 7A's in the future though.

review_title: Good for one time use only for the $
reviews: Could be a little easier to apply these and pull apart when applying them to your drum skin. I really don't know how you would clean these as they collect a lot of debris, when they don't stick all that great in the first place. Good dampener though for those overtones
Love Posca's I love this set as I'm pretty much always using a black for a liner or dark fills. Nice set to have in your Posca Army hehheh

It's a drum key, what more is there to say really. It's a nice key, high quality. Only con for me really was it's top heavy so you can't leave it in your lug while playing or it falls off. I like to just have Mikey handy on the lug ready to go. Not a big deal though!
Nice case, great quality Made by Nikon

True to size. I'm 6ft. 3 and I usually wear a size 11.5 to a 12, but always stick to a 11.5 in online purchases. Excellent quality as expected from Timberland and got these on Sale! So double bonus. If you know anything about Nike ACG boots from the 90's these are a very similar cut. Nice hiking boot, comfortable and sturdy. Cons: the insoles are paper thin. I'd order a good pair of insoles for these boots to go the extra mile.
Good to have for keys or a camera/ cellphone. Multi purpose and good quality.

review_title: Not a good fit for New Balance shoes
reviews: Great shoelaces and I have these in my Chuck Taylors in a 57'? So I grabbed these knowing the sturdiness and quality of the shoelace itself. But! Sadly the ends are to thick to put through my new Balance sneakers. They don't fit the eye lights at all, even if I forced them in. So sadly I cant use these and have to return them.

Great shirts for work or to do personal art on. Heavy cotton, comfy and simple. They shrink quite a bit, so I'd air dry when there a bit damp out of the dryer to maintain shape. Cons the wrist are a bit tight on the long sleeve, but I can't really complain for the cost of quality. Great shirts I'm 6ft. 3 and a Large fits me properly.
Fun toy for my nephew, he's a little young for it. But I'm sure he will appreciate it more in a year or so.

review_title: Warm Feet / happy I bought these
reviews: Comfy like the other Superfeet insoles. True to size and they keep you warm for those chilly days. Super easy to swap over to my other Superfeet flex in the hotter / warmer days. Get a pair!
Favourite insoles. Been wearing Superfeet insoles for atleast 8 years?? Definitely worth every penny

review_title: Amazing and Simplistic boots / practical and stylish
reviews: Renewing my 5 year old 558's these are a little slimmer. But I know they stretch out and form fit to your feet. So no complaints. Easy return as I ordered the rustic black first and found them to be too matte and grey for my preference. Awesome boots! Never owning any other brand of leather boots. This is my 3rd pair in 12 year's. If you take care of them they last forever.

review_title: Works, just a couple things you should know.
reviews: Used it on a old pair of Blundstones. High sheen even without a buff. It should specify that it has a sheen to it or if it's a neutral matte polish. Other pet peeve was it came with no polishing clothe. So me ordering black I had to go out and buy one. Other than that. Works well. Easy to use and most of all makes your leather boots looking brand new.

review_title: Ok for arts and crafts for children. Not professional art
reviews: Crappy quality. Leaks and the brushes are a little bent in the caps.

review_title: Good accessory for a seat lock
reviews: Thought this was a little thicker for a wheel loop to my U lock but it's very thin and as shown on the box it's more so for a quick release seat. Good to have tho either way. Thieves definitely know your bike is locked up with the bright kryptonite logo. Always have used kryptonite locks, never disappointed..
Color is blotchy when applied and dries darker
Wish these came in a larger variety of sizes for flat and round. Quality laces, wearing these on my Chucks
Nice!

review_title: Decent print, bad sizing and low quality material
reviews: Ok design. Tshirt was a little too small length wise and the sleeves were too long for a Tshirt. I got this as Daniel Johnston just passed away. But yeah I'd rather just order from his site. Not a total let down. My girlfriend has a new shirt.

Classic Cotton Gildan shirts. Sturdy and durable as anticipated. Any good band shirt I've owned that's lasted was a Gildan Tshirt. So I'm going to put these 2 shirts to the test at work and they might just be my new Go To Tshirt.
There ok
Comfy quality shirt. True to size. I'm 6/3 180lbs the size Large was a perfect fit not too baggy, not too tight. Buy this if you're a drummer supporting quality percussion products

Broke in a week.

Plastic casing. So if paint get on the gauge do use a thinner or you will fog up the casing and not be able to see the psi your spraying

Got these and they are way too small. Asked for a refund from seller and was offered $4.00 and to keep these useless unsafe handlebars as they wanted to avoid me paying shipping cost. Pointless. Also advised me to give them to a family member or something if I wasn't going to use them? Terrible sales representative who got back to me. Dont buy these unless your buying them for a small child.

Cheaply made product from Bodum, I got this fir my girlfriend as she prefers french press coffee over the bulky coffeemaker. Had it for a month and the screen/ filter broke and it's now a useless french press. Because the coffee grinds float up through the unsealed filter press. Waste of money!

Nicely packaged, excellent Japanese products as usual. I have yet to use these, but I trust they will just as good as the ones I purchased locally. Order from Japan when buying Posca markers. 1. You're getting what you want from the main source (Japan) 2. You're saving money on a amazing product from Japan. Hope to buy more from this seller in the future. Great product made in Japan 100% Quality guaranteed. :)
Not the greatest design. But it's a durable air blower. Good price too

review_title: Sizing. I'm 6/3 and have had a large and realised a year later that a medium is a proper fit.
reviews: Light weight, easy to use and less hot on summer days than most 3M mask. The quick last system is a bonus if working with others to speak without taking the entire mask off. My go to mask.
Garbage. Unless you want to be a walking dust collector these suits are are like paper and useless in a paint booth or for any DIY jobs.

review_title: Awesome price, great Bike! Faulty parts!!
reviews: Great lightweight bike fuel the cost. Very sleek and the black matte color looks awesome. Have had tons of compliments and inquiries as to where I got it. Got a full tune up when I first purchased this bike a year ago. I bike alot with this (almost daily) Ihaven't had a flat or any issues. Up until yesterday I was biking and coming down a hill and the coaster break popped out of the frame and jolted me forward almost hitting a car. This could have been fatal so now I dont know how to fix my bike or replace that part. So if I could get a replacement part or something that would be AMAZING!

review_title: Nice, handy tool to have for crossroad trips biking
reviews: Compact for the road, easy to use, nice grip on handle.
I've used this bike lubricant for years. A must have to keep your chain protected from the elements.
Easy to use. Bags last awhile and dont fill up as fast as other vacuum bags.

review_title: Presta valve adapter built in pump head.
reviews: Great pump. Includes two valves on tip. You don't need to purchase those cheap little presta valves for your bike tires and or other presta valved tubes. It's got a accurate PSI gauge and comes with a mattress and ball adapter. Great pump.
Easy to use DWR spray. I had troubles with the spray trigger at first, but it ended up working after getting some air flow.
